# LDOC - LibreGrad Documentation Compiler

LDOC is a simple, lightweight documentation format and compiler designed for easy writing and publishing of technical documentation with extended markdown-like syntax and custom commands.

---

## Features

- Markdown-style headings (`#`, `##`, `###`)
- Inline code and fenced code blocks with syntax highlighting
- Special commands:
  - `@include PATH` — recursively include external files
  - `@var NAME=VALUE` — define variables for substitution
  - `@if VAR=VALUE ... @endif` — conditional content blocks
  - `@command: YOUR COMMAND` — render shell/console commands as highlighted code
  - `@codeblock LANG NAME ... @endcodeblock` — reusable named code blocks
  - `@usecode NAME` — insert named code blocks
  - `@image: URL "ALT TEXT"` — embed images
  - `@video: URL` — embed videos
  - `@note:`, `@warning:`, `@info:`, `@tip:`, `@todo:` — special stylized blocks
  - `@badge: TYPE|TEXT|CLASS` — badges for highlights
  - `@table: ... @endtable` — markdown-style tables

---

## Installation

Clone the repository and make sure you have Python 3 installed:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/ternicincl/ldoc.git
cd ldoc
```
Compile a single .ldoc file:

./ldoc.py build examples/sample.ldoc -o build

Compile all .ldoc files in a directory:

./ldoc.py build docs/ -o build